rlm-gcp-project-open

Browse all GCP projects accessible to the current gcloud account via
fzf and open the selected project in the GCP console.

Projects are fetched with "gcloud projects list" and include every
project visible to the active gcloud credential. Previously selected
projects float to the top of the list, most recent first.

CACHING
  The project list is cached in ~/.cache/gcp-project-open/projects.txt.
  Selection history is recorded in ~/.cache/gcp-project-open/history.txt
  and used to re-sort the list on each invocation.

  On the first run the list is fetched from GCP; subsequent runs load
  instantly from the cache.

  The fzf header shows how old the cache is. To refresh it, select
  the "--- REFRESH CACHE ---" entry at the top of the list; this
  deletes the cache file and re-fetches all projects before re-opening
  the picker.

On selection the function:
  1. Prints the GCP console URL to stdout.
  2. Copies the URL to the clipboard (pbcopy on macOS,
     xclip/xsel on Linux).
  3. Opens the URL in the system browser (open on macOS,
     xdg-open on Linux).

The fzf preview pane shows project details via
"gcloud projects describe".

Requires: gcloud (Google Cloud SDK), fzf.
